Computing Best Fit Line Path

Start:
w = 1
b = 1
        ↓

Compute predictions:
ŷ = wx + b

        ↓

Calculate Cost:
J(w,b) = (1/2m) Σ(ŷ(i) - y(i))²

        ↓

Calculate gradients:
dw = (1/m) Σ(ŷ(i) - y(i))x(i)

db = (1/m) Σ(ŷ(i) - y(i))

        ↓

Update parameters:
w = w - αdw
b = b - αdb

        ↓

New w and b obtained

        ↓

Compute new predictions:
